Fourteen years after its last review, Ogun State Government has concluded the Review and Amendment of Guidelines on Administrative Procedures for Local Councils, to accelerate development at the grassroots.
 
While receiving the report of the Committee in his office, the Commissioner for Local Government and Chieftaincy Affairs, Afolabi Afuape said the reviewed guidelines, when made official would be one of the major achievements of the ministry.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .